Text.Value: All right then, let's get going. I'm [GEN_PlayerName_c11eee1e-7815-6143-7233-f2427799fa53].

EditorData.logicalname: AFTER REACTION TO GITH IN PARTY

Text.Value: I know enough. But I'll risk it over certain death.

EditorData.NodeContext: Spoken with some aggression.She's convinced gith are bad news.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Shadowheart is on her knees, having just been ejected from her pod. She gets to her feet

Text.Value: Sounds in line with what I've heard about your kind.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Shadowheart reaches into her pod and fetches an ornate box. She quickly puts it away, and leaves

Text.Value: We both need all the help we can get. Let's try get off this thing together.
A curious tone, for one who owes her life to me.
Trust me, I'll keep up.
First you beg for help, then cast suspicion on me, and now you want to join me? You are an odd one.
*Your mind lurches into her thoughts. Her gratitude is mixed with wariness - because you're a gith.*
*Your mind lurches into her thoughts. Her gratitude is mixed with wariness - because you look like a gith.*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: SH and the player react to a psionic mind meld
EditorData.InternalNodeContext: SH and the player react to a psionic mind meld

Text.Value: Got a problem with githyanki?
All right then, come on. I'm [GEN_PlayerName_c11eee1e-7815-6143-7233-f2427799fa53].
I did... It must be because of those parasites they put in us...
I'm getting out of here. Follow me, if you can keep up.
I've changed my mind - you're on your own.

EditorData.logicalname: ALREADY OFFERED TO LET SH JOIN

Text.Value: I'm used to it. Good luck... and thank you, for your help.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: SH runs off, not to be seen again until den recruitment.

Text.Value: You're a gith... why did you help me?

EditorData.logicalname: PLAYER IS OR LOOKS LIKE A GITH

Text.Value: *Your mind lurches into her thoughts. You feel her gratitude, but also guardedness. And above all, a will to survive.*
We both need to get off this thing. Let's help each other.
It's nothing. Trust me.
Very well, come with me. But if you prove a burden, I will leave you behind.
Did you feel that just now? We were in each other's heads.
I'm grateful, but don't expect me to be your pawn just because you freed me.
I'm afraid not. Good luck to you - I'll take my chances alone.
Dangerous company's what you need in a fight.
Come with me, then.
Half-elf. And maybe we should travel together for now... in the interest of survival.
Wait - you're not actually the one in charge of this group, are you? No offence, but I need to speak to a leader. Someone who knows where they're going.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Shadowheart reaches into her pod and fetches an ornate box. She quickly puts it away, and leaves

Text.Value: We need to deal with that, but first we've to get off this thing... let's join up.
Did you feel that just now? We were in each other's heads.
One moment.
You keep dangerous company.
Let me come with you. We can get off this ship, and watch each other's backs along the way.

EditorData.NodeContext: A little caution on 'watch each other's backs' - implying lingering distrust of the gith who's with them

Text.Value: There's no time to spare. Lead the way.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Shadowheart is looking at the player (ie no Lae'zel inclusion occurred).

Text.Value: *Your mind lurches into her thoughts. Her gratitude is mixed with wariness - because you have a gith with you.*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: SH and the player react to a psionic mind meld
EditorData.InternalNodeContext: SH and the player react to a psionic mind meld

Text.Value: I'll have to do, for now.
Are you sure about that? Better odds of surviving if we help each other.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Shadowheart reaches into her pod and fetches an ornate box. She quickly puts it away.|

Text.Value: As I said, we are finished. Go.
That's what your kind does - they take. Still... you did help me.
Did you feel that just now? We were in each other's heads.
You may prove useful to me in getting off this ship - as a decoy in battle, perhaps.
What could the likes of you possibly know of my people?
We are finished. Be on your way, elf. Survive if you can.
Half-elf. Better I go alone, actually. A group your size would slow me down...
Did you feel what I felt just before? We were in each other's heads.
Consider me gone. Maybe I'll see you around - if you survive, that is.
Must I want something?
No, you're on your own.
I think I'll take my chances alone if it's all the same - less conspicuous. Good luck - and thank you.
Like I said, you're on your own.
Agh, my head...
They'll have to wait. I need to get off this ship alive first.
Come on, time to go.
I've changed my mind. Find your own way off this ship.
Not so curious. I've heard what gith are like. Still... you did free me.
She's right. Lead on.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Shadowheart looks at  the player again (had glanced suspiciously at Lae'zel on previous node)

Text.Value: Enough of this chatter. We need to get to the helm - now.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Shadowheart throws a suspicous look at Lae'zel

Text.Value: Gladly. And best of luck. You'll need it.
But that'll have to wait. Are we going to help each other, or not?
I thought that damn thing was going to be my coffin. Thank you -

EditorData.NodeContext: Relieved at being free - cut off at the end (by a mindmeld)

Text.Value: Finally. Let us make for the helm - we've wasted enough time already.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Shadowheart throws a suspicous look at Lae'zel

Text.Value: Why? Because you asked.
I suppose I am. Fitting company for a decidedly odd situation, wouldn't you say?

EditorData.NodeContext: Little bit of wry self-awareness. 'Yes I know I can seem difficult'.

Text.Value: Fair point. Looks like there's plenty of fighting ahead.
Wait - looks like you've a full complement already. We'd make for easy targets, all grouped together like that.
What's that?
You'd better get out of here - it's everyone for themselves.
More that gith have a problem with everyone else. But there's more important matters right now - survival.
Shadowheart. One moment...
And you expect what in return exactly? Githyanki aren't given to charity.

Synopsis: Dialogue with SH after you free her from the pod aboard the nautiloid. You can bring her with you in a bid to escape together, or leave her to fend for herself. Different branches if the player is gith, looks like a gith or has a gith follower/companion. In each case, Shadowheart retrieves the Orpheus box towards the end of the diialogue from her pod, then joins the player or leaves by herself.
